Description: Fix CVE-2026-44490 (GHSA-898c-q2cr-xwhg) prototype-pollution gadget in utils.merge
 axios's utils.merge() reads potential existing values via a bare
 `result[key]` lookup, which walks the prototype chain. When
 Object.prototype has been polluted (or when a user passes an object
 whose prototype has been tampered with), the recursive merge can
 pick up polluted values and copy them into the merged result,
 propagating the pollution into user-visible config/state.
 .
 Guard the read behind Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call() so only
 own properties are considered when deciding whether to recurse.
 .
 Adapted from the sibling 0.27.2 backport for axios 0.31.1. The
 upstream fix also hardens Object.defineProperty descriptors in
 utils.extend, utils.inherits, mergeConfig, AxiosHeaders and the
 adapters registry, but:
   * axios 0.31.1's utils.extend/inherits use direct property
     assignment (a[key] = ..., prototype.constructor = ...) rather
     than Object.defineProperty, so there is no descriptor to harden.
   * axios 0.31.1's mergeConfig uses Object.create(null) plus a
     utils.hasOwnProperty helper — it never calls Object.defineProperty
     on the config, so there is no descriptor to harden.
   * lib/core/AxiosHeaders.js and lib/adapters/adapters.js do not
     exist yet in 0.31.1 (added in later 1.x releases).
 The residual gadget in this line-of-code is the merge() prototype
 walk, which this patch fixes.
Origin: internal-reuse, patches/reference/CVE-2026-44490.patch (sibling axios 0.27.2)
Bug: https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-898c-q2cr-xwhg
Last-Update: 2026-07-02

--- a/lib/utils.js
+++ b/lib/utils.js
@@ -328,8 +328,12 @@ function merge(/* obj1, obj2, obj3, ... */) {
       return;
     }

-    if (isPlainObject(result[key]) && isPlainObject(val)) {
-      result[key] = merge(result[key], val);
+    // Read via own-prop only — a bare `result[key]` walks the prototype
+    // chain, so a polluted Object.prototype value could surface here and
+    // get copied into the merged result. See GHSA-898c-q2cr-xwhg.
+    var existing = Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(result, key) ? result[key] : undefined;
+    if (isPlainObject(existing) && isPlainObject(val)) {
+      result[key] = merge(existing, val);
     } else if (isPlainObject(val)) {
       result[key] = merge({}, val);
     } else if (isArray(val)) {

